Put a #frying pan{} on high heat and add the @pine nuts{25}(no oil). Toast for a couple of
minutes until golden, shaking the pan to avoid them burning. Remove the pan from the
heat and tip the pine nuts into a small #bowl{}. Halve, peel and roughly chop the
@onion{1}. Remove the top and bottom from the @carrot{1} and coarsely grate (no need
to peel). Quarter the @chestnut mushrooms{150}. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(or
use a garlic press).

Return the frying pan to medium heat with a drizzle of @olive oil{}. Add the onion and
mushrooms and cook, stirring, until soft, ~{4-5%mins}. Add the @Worcester sauce{15} to
reduce by half then add the @finely chopped tomatoes{1}(with onion and garlic),
@red wine stock paste{28} and @water{50}. Bring to the boil, stirring to dissolve the
stock pot. Lower the heat to medium and stir in the carrot. Simmer until thick and
tomatoey, ~{10-12%mins}.

Put a large #saucepan{} of water with a pinch of @salt{} on to boil for the squoodles.
Meanwhile, roughly chop the @basil{12}(stalks and all). Pop the toasted pine nuts into a
#freezer bag{} and bash with the base of a saucepan. Return to the bowl and add half the
basil. Gradually stir in a little @olive oil{} until you have a thick drizzling
consistency.

When your bolognese is nearly ready, and the water is boiling. Add the
@butternut squash noodles{350} to the water and cook until tender, ~{2-3%mins}. When
cooked, drain into a #colander{} then return to the saucepan and season with @salt{}
and plenty of @pepper{}. Stir through half the drizzle.

Stir the remaining basil through the bolognese. Taste and add salt and pepper if
necessary.

Serve the butternut squash noodles in bowls topped with a helping of bolognese. Finish
with the remaining basil and pine nut drizzle. Enjoy!